  "prompt": "What is organisms?",
  "response": "Organisms are individual living entities that can carry out processes necessary for life. They range from simple single-celled forms, like bacteria and archaea, to complex multicellular forms, such as plants, animals, fungi, and protists. Organisms are characterized by their ability to grow, reproduce, respond to stimuli, and carry out various metabolic activities. They are classified into various taxonomic groups based on their shared characteristics and evolutionary relationships. Each organism has a unique set of genetic material that dictates its structure, function, and behavior.",
